                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17214734" author="edimitrova" created="Thu, 15 Oct 2020 14:21:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is that it was possible to open a new Keyspace instance in the middle of Schema.dropKeyspace(). To see the problem the drop has to progress to the following &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-3.11/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/config/Schema.java#L657&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;state&lt;/a&gt;: 1) Keyspace instance doesn&apos;t exist - it has been already removed. &lt;br/&gt;
 2) KeyspaceMetadata still exists&lt;br/&gt;
 Keyspace.open in this state creates a new Keyspace instance (with ColumnFamilyStore instances) and stores it in Schema.keyspaceInstances. This is an object leak.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/pull/59&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.11 &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CI run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jenkins-cm4.apache.org/job/Cassandra-devbranch/104/#showFailuresLink&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Java8 &lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT: Not applicable to 4.0&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/pull/62&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;4.0 &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;CI run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/414/workflows/9d0905bd-6ca6-480a-862b-35d5842ed5ef&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Java 8 &lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/414/workflows/9476a603-a494-4da3-bf69-9498d40ae29a&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Java 11 &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17216764" author="michaelsembwever" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2020 14:23:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think you were right originally about this patch not applying to 4.0. The call hierarchy to the private &lt;tt&gt;Schema.dropKeyspace(..)&lt;/tt&gt;  method is only three only methods, all of which are &lt;tt&gt;synchronized&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 3.11: at runtime it&apos;s only accessed by method in &lt;tt&gt;SchemaKeyspace.mergeSchema(..)&lt;/tt&gt;  which is also &lt;tt&gt;synchronized&lt;/tt&gt;. But the method itself is public and not &lt;tt&gt;synchronized&lt;/tt&gt; so the tests can get into the race condition. Ideally i would think it&apos;s better to have synchronized at the test layer, but that&apos;s maybe asking a bit much for such a small fix, so I&apos;m +1 on the 3.11 patch. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17216939" author="edimitrova" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2020 17:15:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed, as per my initial comment - 	schema race conditions solved for 4.0 with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9425&quot; title=&quot;Make node-local schema fully immutable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9425&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9425&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt;!!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17217385" author="michaelsembwever" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2020 07:31:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed as &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/bca91ca84b9daf8b9e3d361975a535b90b4f77fa&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;bca91ca84b9daf8b9e3d361975a535b90b4f77fa&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
